My God, how many are my fears!
They build a fortress round my soul,
A labyrinth of whispered tears,
Where shadows play a silent role.

But through the maze, a path appears,
Lit by the flicker of my will,
A song that rises through the years,
A promise that my heart can fill.

For fear is but a fleeting guest,
A visitor who comes to teach,
That courage grows within the quest,
Beyond the limits we beseech.

My God, how many are my fears!
Yet still I walk, despite the years.
